This article is a notice from the President regarding the continuation of the national emergency with respect to North Korea. The President declared a national emergency in 2008 due to the threat of the proliferation of weapons-usable fissile material on the Korean Peninsula. This national emergency has been expanded in scope over the years to address the threat to national security, foreign policy, and the economy of the United States posed by the actions and policies of the Government of North Korea. The President has signed executive orders to maintain certain restrictions and import limitations to deal with this national emergency. The President has determined that the national emergency and the measures taken to address it must continue beyond June 26, 2011. Therefore, the national emergency declared in 2008 will be continued for another year.